he politics behind their institutional design, and investigates the behavior of the ICC. Through the development and empirical testing of several theoretical frameworks, Power and Principle helps us better understand the factors that resulted in the emergence of international criminal courts and helps us determine the broader implications of their presence in society.  afunded by Knowledge Unlatched  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aNational securityzUnited States. 0aStatesmenzUnited StatesvBiography. 4aInternational Studies. 4aLegal History & Studies. 4aPolitical Science & Political History.  ainstitutional power, prerogatives, control, human rights, International Criminal Court, institutionalization, genocide, war crimes, crimes against humanity, activism.2 aKnowledge Unlatchedefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066587140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/9781501708428?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501708428423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501708428/original  a978-3-11-066587-1  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles